# Claude Workspace Rules

These rules apply to Claude (Claude Code, Cursor, or other integrations) when working on the Palovsky workspace.

## 1. Project Initialization & Context Alignment
- **Read Project Context on Startup**: Before executing any code modifications, research, or planning, you **MUST** read [PROJECT_CONTEXT.md](file:///Users/naufal/Desktop/coding/local-test/PROJECT_CONTEXT.md) to align with the current workspace structure and component layout.

## 2. Maintenance of PROJECT_CONTEXT.md
- **Mandatory Updates**: You **MUST** update [PROJECT_CONTEXT.md](file:///Users/naufal/Desktop/coding/local-test/PROJECT_CONTEXT.md) whenever you make structural changes to the project, including:
  - Creating new files or directories.
  - Deleting/removing files or directories.
  - Renaming or relocating existing files or directories.
  - Modifying major component architecture (e.g. merging files, splitting styles).
- **Format Consistency**: Keep the file tree representation and component breakdowns accurate and clean when editing the context file.

## 3. Styling Guidelines
- **Tokens and Variables**: Always check and use the tokens defined in [index.css](file:///Users/naufal/Desktop/coding/local-test/src/index.css).
- **New Properties**: If you introduce any new custom properties or design tokens, they must be declared inside [index.css](file:///Users/naufal/Desktop/coding/local-test/src/index.css) instead of inline or inside component-specific stylesheets.
